{"word":"Σαλμακίς","slug":"Σαλμακίς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n93154\" key=\"*salmaki/s\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Σαλμᾰκίς</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ίδος</itype>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ἡ</gen>, a district in Halicarnassus, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ SIG\">SIG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">46.24</biblScope> </bibl> <date TEIform=\"date\">(v B.C.)</date>; also a fountain there, said to cause sexual weakness and associated with Hermaphroditus, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001.perseus-grc1:14:2:16\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Str.\">Str.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14.2.16</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Vitr.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.8.11</biblScope></bibl>, Ov.<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">Met.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.286</biblScope> </bibl>: hence <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">σαλμᾰκίδες</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">αἱ</gen>, a name for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἑταῖραι</foreign> (so <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Suid.</author> </bibl>) or effeminate men, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">AP</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">7.222</biblScope> </bibl> (<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Phld.\">Phld.</a></author> </bibl>).</entryFree>"}]}